body:
This is expected as ONNX's GraphProto message doesn't support storing initializers of type `SequenceProto`. It only supports storing `TensorProto` and `SparseTensorProto` initializers currently (https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/ee4888c24510787bb8c61ebcba43ef252744e648/onnx/onnx.in.proto#L449). So even if this node can be folded there is currently not a way to store the "constant" result as an initializer in the `GraphProto` instance. We would have to find other ways to hold them in the runtime. 

Maybe we can make the message a bit less jarring (i.e.) it doesn't need to be a warning log for sequence types.

Thank you @hariharans29 for your response. I understand. Do you see a value in extending ONNX's GraphProto to store sequence initializers as well? Can you please help me understand the potential performance benefits that we could gain from having constant folding support for sequences? I could bring this up for discussion with the relevant ONNX groups. If you don't see value in it, I guess that making this a log and not a warning for sequence types would make sense.

issue.body:
# Ask a Question

### Question
Is there a good reason why GraphProto doesn't have a sequence initializers field (like it is the case for tensors and sparse tensors)?

### Further information
- Relevant Area (*e.g. model usage, backend, best practices, converters, shape_inference, version_converter, training, test, operators*):
 GraphProto definitions

- Is this issue related to a specific model?  
**Model name** (*e.g. mnist*): NA  
**Model opset** (*e.g. 7*): NA

### Notes

To give you some context, it was spotted during the use of SequenceEmpty with ONNX Runtime: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11041

Having support for sequence initializers would enable constant folding.

body:
Can we do treat this as two separate issues:
(a) Can we change ORT to eliminate or simplify this message? It is a minor optimization (which is not dependent on ONNX anyway ... a backend can choose to optimize this away in any way it chooses).
(b) Extending the proto definition to support sequence initializers could, independently, be useful. Liqun has a PR for this in ONNX (https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/4148 ); would it be straightforward for onnxruntime to support such an extension?
Has there been any action on @gramalingam's suggestion a) above, on removing the warning message? We have had another customer confused by this message.
